			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify;  background-color: #000016;   background-image: none;  background-repeat: repeat-x; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I map my song gems to hot keys.&nbsp; So, to start a song, I hit that hot key.&nbsp; To start the next song, I hit that same hot key (stop song)&nbsp;then hit the next song to start.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Basically, this turns into 1...12...23...31... key pad hitting to get twisting done.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It&nbsp;would really be niffty if clicking a new song would stop the previous song from playing and start the song you just clicked.&nbsp; Clicking the same song that is playing would stop songs all togeather.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My twist could turn into 1...2...3...1...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I know the first response is going to be "well, you could macro /stopsong, /startsong 1 ..."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Unfortunately, as soon as you add clicky effects combined with missed notes and lag, macros just wont work.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Now, there's gonna be bards that like to do it the old way (double clicking and stuff), so, if it was added in, it should be an option that we can set in our ini file.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Saving half the keystrokes (for me) would be a huge win and help my wrists out a lot.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Thanks for listening.</DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p><i>- <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22184">Tremelo</a>  <br><font color="FF00FF">Bard Class Correspondent</font></i>
							</div>
																
