						<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#0C142B" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<P>"<EM>Which can be done with as me and others have pointed out with the simple macro "/stopsong, /cast #". This macro is not affected by lag or missed notes, and also allows you quickly adapt to changed situations. It's the complicated macros for more than one song per keypress or using gamepads which can't deal with all that</EM>."</P>
<P>It's a matter of combining macros with clicky items.&nbsp;&nbsp; *If* you're clicky item is in slot 4, and you use a macro in slot 3 (twist being 1.. 2.. 3.. 4..), you're slot 3 macro has to look like : /stopsong, /cast #, /pause 30, /stopsong... That one macro is very prone to lag and missed notes.&nbsp; That's the macro you'd use in conjunction with clickies.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P><EM>"Gamepads and Macro's work fine for clicky items</EM>."</P>
<P>Honestly, I don't know much about game pads.&nbsp; Being a bard who's been playing since release, I'm kinda set in my ways about twisting.&nbsp; If I'm not twisting, I don't feel like I'm playing.</P>
<P>But, what happens on a gamepad when you miss a note?&nbsp; Or two?&nbsp; Or four?</P>
<P>And are you proposing that the way EQ should be played is to purchase a gamepad and then use a workaround to single click songs and still not have a garantee to recover from missed notes?</P>
<P>You keep your spell gems up.&nbsp; I don't.&nbsp; That's the point of a customizable UI.&nbsp; You can have it your way and I can have it mine.&nbsp; Macros are just work arounds.&nbsp; Enough people are using them to implicate that the UI should accomodate changes.&nbsp; That's what good UI's do... make it easy for the user to interface with application.</P>
<P>Adding the feature I'm suggesting doesn't effect people who like using macro's or gamepads.&nbsp; Use them all day long.&nbsp; They just arent for me (and problably a lot of other people).&nbsp; I want a fix for the macro workaround.&nbsp; That is all.</P>
