			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<P>I've used the /stopsong, /cast macros since level 20.&nbsp; They in NO WAY effect my twisting other then to cut down on needless keypresses.&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>My hotkey bank has Gems 1 through 4 in slots 1 through 4.&nbsp; Slot 5 is a non-macro'd mez, slot 6 Songblade.&nbsp; Rest are utility.&nbsp; If i need to click songblade its not too hard to hit 5 then 6.&nbsp; </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>With a gamepad it'd be the same way.&nbsp; Your macro is running, twisting songs 1 through 4.&nbsp; You can set 1 key to say hit hotkey 5, then hotkey 6.&nbsp; Hotkey 5 will stop your song, 6 will click songblade, and your twist will continue when songbalde is done casting.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>I do agree that it would be wonderful if SoE cut down on some keystrokes.&nbsp; TCH had a great thread on making auto-twisting an AA.&nbsp; But after spending points on CF 3 and Internal Metronome 5 I wouldnt count on it.</P>
