<P>"<EM>My hotkey bank has Gems 1 through 4 in slots 1 through 4.&nbsp; Slot 5 is a non-macro'd mez, slot 6 Songblade.&nbsp; Rest are utility.&nbsp; If i need to click songblade its not too hard to hit 5 then 6.&nbsp;</EM> "</P>
<P>Nobody uses songblades in their normal twists.&nbsp; But people do use lute of flowing water (instaclick winds of marr) or drums of rathe (3 second cast for chant of plague).</P>
<P>Assuming Slot4 is non-hotkeyed song (or macro'd /stopsong only).&nbsp; Slot 5 is lute.&nbsp; Slot 6 is drums.</P>
<P>Lets say we were going to use your method of twisting.</P>
<P>Lute in twist: 1... 2... 3... <U>451... 2... 3</U>... 451... (5 keys, 4 effects)</P>
<P>Drums in twist: 1... 2... 3... <U>4641... 2... 3</U>... 4641... (6 keys, 4 effects)</P>
<P>Lute and drums in twist: 1... 2... 3... <U>456... 41... 2... 3</U>... 4546... (7 keys,&nbsp;5 effects)</P>
<P>Using non-macro'd twist:</P>
<P>Lute in twist: 1... 12... 23... <U>351... 12... 23</U>... 351... (7 keys, 4 effects)</P>
<P>Drums in twist: 1... 12... 23... <U>36... 11... 12... 23</U>... 36... (8 keys, 4 effects)</P>
<P>Lute and drums in twist: 1... 12... 23... <U>356... 41... 12... 23</U>... 356... (9 keys,&nbsp;5 effects)</P>
<P>The way I am proposing:</P>
<P>Lute in twist: 1... 2... 3... <U>51... 2... 3</U>... 51... (4 keys, 4 effects)</P>
<P>Drums in twist: 1... 2... 3... <U>6... 1... 2... 3</U>... 6... (4 keys, 4 effects)</P>
<P>Lute and drums in twist: 1... 2... 3... <U>56... 1... 2... 3</U>... 56... (5 keys,&nbsp;5 effects)</P>
<P>Do you see now how macro'ing with clicky items reduces some keystrokes, but not really that many?&nbsp; Considering there are a few other items out there which we will use with clicky effect (like the flute with warmarch), the twists will become more complicatied and more keys strokes even with macros.</P>
<P>A couple of question that you gamepad pushers aren't answering.&nbsp; </P>
<P>1. When you miss a note, is that song gone for that twist cycle?&nbsp;</P>
<P>2. If you have serverlag (or spiked lag), don't you have to adjust your pause time on your gamepad?&nbsp; If you don't wont you miss songs?</P></DIV>
																																		<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 100; overflow: hidden;">
														<p><i>- <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22184">Tremelo</a>  <br><font color="FF00FF">Bard Class Correspondent</font></i>
