			<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; " >
												<DIV></DIV>
<P>Yeah it being the lute for an instant mana-shot would kinda throw a wrench in it.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Most gamepads dont watch a log to see missed notes.&nbsp; You would just record keystrokes.&nbsp; So it just hits keyboard keys.&nbsp; 1, 2, 3, a, b, c whatever.&nbsp; And then you can set your own timing, say .1 second keypress then wait 2.6 seconds then repeat with a new key and so on.&nbsp; So with missed notes you have to turn off the macro (one key) and finish the twist till the beginning and hitting the start macro button.&nbsp; My buddy has one for one of those new 1st person shooters.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>BTW, has there been any firm word on if running a gamepad with macros is against the EULA?&nbsp; My doc is near to requiring one now, LoL.</P>
